<concept>
With the following notation next to an object:<br>
<img src="Sectionals/5540_MSL_650_AGL.jpg">
A blue number not in parentheses, indicates the altitude of the top of an
object with respect to mean sea level (MSL).  A blue number within parentheses
indicates the altitude above the ground (AGL).  In this case, the top of the
object is 5540 feet MSL or 650 feet AGL.
<question permute="XXX">
    If the following appeared next to an object:<br>
    <img src="Sectionals/5540_MSL_650_AGL.jpg"><br>
    What is the altitude XXX of the top of the object?
    <answer for="above mean sea level (MSL)">5540</answer>
    <answer for="above ground level (AGL)">650</answer>
</question></concept>

<concept>
With the following notation next to an object:<br>
<img src="Sectionals/5540_MSL_650_AGL.jpg">
A blue number not in parentheses, indicates the altitude of the top of an
object with respect to mean sea level (MSL).  A blue number within parentheses
indicates the altitude above the ground (AGL).  In this case, the top of the
object is 5540 feet MSL or 650 feet AGL.
<question permute="XXX">
    <img src="Sectionals/Garfield_stack.jpg"><br>
    How many feet XXX?
    <answer for="is the top of Garfield stack above mean sea level (MSL)">5540</answer>
    <answer for="is the top of Garfield stack above ground level (AGL)">650</answer>
    <answer for="is the bottom of Garfield stack above mean sea level (MSL)">4890</answer>
    <answer for="is the bottom of Garfield stack above ground level (AGL)">0</answer>
</question></concept>

<concept>
A large blue number followed by a small blue digit shows the highest altitude
in this section of the map in hundreds of feet above mean sea level (MSL).
For instance:<br>
<img src="Sectionals/Maximum_elevation.jpg"><br>
means that the highest tourain in the section is 12,500 feet.
<question>
    <img src="Sectionals/Maximum_elevation.jpg"><br>
    means that the highest tourain in this section is:
    <answer>12.5 feet</answer>
    <answer>125 feet</answer>
    <answer>1250 feet</answer>
    <answer>12500 feet</answer>
</question></concept>
